  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to explore the recurrence risk of cardiovascular events in
      patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus and coronary heart disease after different
      antidiabetic drug therapy (glipizide or metformin) by using an double-blind, randomized,
      parallel control and prospective study

      The end point of this study is:

        1. follow up 3yr

        2. recurrence of cardiovascular event

        3. death caused by other reasons such as stroke, uremia, blindness and amputation
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
